{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"151b43fb-f2f2-4053-ac41-cdf5201b7fec","content":"Here are the issues I found in this `template.json`:\n\n1. **Missing `identity`** (required) — every template needs a unique `identity` field.\n\n2. **`defaultValue` mismatch on `targetFramework`** — the default is `\"net7.0\"` but that isn't listed in `choices` (only `net8.0` and `net9.0` are).\n\n3. **Invalid `defaultValue` on `maxRetries`** — datatype is `int` but the default is `\"abc\"` (not a valid integer).\n\n4. **`enableLogging` default** — minor: for `bool` the canonical values are `\"true\"`/`\"false\"`, not `\"yes\"`. Some engines accept it, but `\"true\"` is safer.\n\n5. **`computed1` missing `value`** — computed symbols require a `value` expression.\n\n6. **`generated1` missing `generator`** — generated symbols require a `generator` (e.g., `\"guid\"`, `\"now\"`).\n\n7. **`postActions` entry missing `actionId`** — each post-action needs an `actionId` (e.g., `\"210D431B-A78B-4D2F-B762-4ED3E3EA9025\"` for restore).\n\n8. **Missing `sourceName`** — not strictly required, but without it no name replacement will occur during instantiation.\n\nWould you like me to fix these?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fc121999-0126-482e-8a35-17ab64b35c9d","outputTokens":340,"requestId":"5020:1E3C:27ADA6A:2B99FC5:69FBE3D4"},"id":"30375d14-c04e-4df0-ab67-b595af417a56","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:59:12.066Z","parentId":"9f1f2491-72cf-47fa-bbfe-3228da67e4e9"}
